p.note: Top of page, in a contemporary hand: a few words, trimmed and illegible; top left corner in pencil by a modern hand: A 200; top right corner, in pencil by a modern hand: I; centre page, in pencil by a modern hand: Liber Cartusiae Erfordiensis and a table of contents; bottom right corner: ; right margin, perpendicularly, in a contemporary hand: pen trials (homo quidam Homo quidam fecit cenam magnam et misit seruum suum huius huius) and some writing above, trimmed and illegible; bottom right corner, in ink by a modern hand, a note on the accession of the manuscript: Inköpt till Kgl. Bibliotheket från G. Stephens 23/10 1848; bottom of page, upside down in ink by a contemporary hand: pen trials, partially trimmed (dum hic dum?).

msItem.explicit: fugiat ergo qui saluari desiderat ut penas eterna intolerabiles et horribiles declinet et evadat et regnum amenum et iocundum cum sanctis et electis eorum meritis et precibus possideat Quod nobis prestare dignetur qui patre et spiritu sancto regnat per infinita secula seculorum Amen
